    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I agree that it's use is probably limited in the default mods due to ammo conservation and no one-hit kills, so I'm fine with having it disabled by default if that is the consensus. However, considering that aircraft are on hold-fire stance by default, what is actually the disadvantage to allowing it?\r\n\r\nAnother question: If opportunity fire is disabled, sticky targeting should then also be disabled, correct? Maybe even put it on the same yaml parameter?"
